---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Contact"
  description="Contact Betting Maths with questions, feedback, calculator suggestions or corrections."
>
  <section class="content-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">Contact Betting Maths</p>
    <h1>Contact</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Have feedback, spotted an issue, or want to suggest a new calculator or guide? Use this page to get in touch.
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Important:</strong> Betting Maths cannot provide betting tips, predictions, personalised betting advice or help with gambling losses.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>What you can contact us about</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths is still growing, so feedback is useful. You can get in touch about:
    </p>

    <ul class="standard-list">
      <li>Calculator errors or rounding issues.</li>
      <li>Suggestions for new calculators.</li>
      <li>Betting jargon or glossary terms that should be added.</li>
      <li>Guide topics you would like explained.</li>
      <li>Broken links or page formatting problems.</li>
      <li>General feedback about the site.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Contact details</h2>
    <p>
      Add your preferred contact email address here before publishing the site publicly.
    </p>

    <div class="contact-box">
      <h3>Email</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>Replace this with your email address</strong>
      </p>
      <p class="muted">
        Example: hello@bettingmaths.co.uk
      </p>
    </div>

    <p>
      If you do not want to publish a personal email address, you could create a dedicated address for the site, such as:
    </p>

    <ul class="standard-list">
      <li>hello@bettingmaths.co.uk</li>
      <li>contact@bettingmaths.co.uk</li>
      <li>support@bettingmaths.co.uk</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>What we cannot help with</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths is an educational calculator site. We cannot help with:
    </p>

    <ul class="standard-list">
      <li>Choosing bets or giving tips.</li>
      <li>Predicting results.</li>
      <li>Recovering gambling losses.</li>
      <li>Providing personalised financial or gambling advice.</li>
      <li>Resolving account issues with bookmakers or betting exchanges.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Need gambling support?</h2>
    <p>
      If gambling is causing stress, debt, secrecy, arguments, or a feeling that you cannot stop, please visit the <a href="/responsible-gambling/">Responsible Gambling</a> page for support resources.
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Reminder:</strong> Betting calculators can explain numbers, but they cannot remove risk or guarantee profit.
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .article-section {
      margin-top: 1.25rem;
    }

    .standard-list {
      padding-left: 1.3rem;
    }

    .standard-list li {
      margin: 0.45rem 0;
    }

    .contact-box {
      margin: 1rem 0;
      padding: 1.2rem;
      border: 1px solid rgba(31, 138, 91, 0.35);
      border-radius: 14px;
      background: #eef8f3;
    }

    .contact-box h3 {
      margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    }

    .contact-box p {
      margin: 0.35rem 0;
    }

    .muted {
      color: var(--color-muted);
    }

    .article-section a {
      color: var(--color-green-dark);
      font-weight: 800;
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 3px;
    }
  </style>
</MainLayout>
